<DocsLayout title="MCP server" currentSlug="mcp-server">
  <h1>MCP server</h1>
  <p>
    <code>src-tauri/crates/cc-mcp</code> exposes CommandCenter's tool
    surface over MCP (stdio and HTTP) for external clients, built on the
    <code>rmcp</code> crate. The Tauri app spawns it on its own thread at
    startup, listening on <code>127.0.0.1:7080</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Stub tools</h2>
  <p>
    It currently ships 89 stub tools mirroring Solo's full tool surface,
    across nine domains: Session, Projects, Processes, Scratchpads, Todos,
    Locks, Timers, Prompt Templates, and Feedback. Every tool has a
    complete parameter schema and is discoverable via <code>tools/list</code>,
    but handlers return "Not yet implemented."
  </p>

  <h2>Transport</h2>
  <p>
    Supports both a dual-framing stdio transport (newline-delimited JSON
    for Claude Code/Cursor, Content-Length-framed JSON-RPC for
    Codex/OpenCode) and a streamable HTTP transport.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
